    <h1>BLT Sandwich Recipe</h1>
    <p>The BLT Sandwich is one of the most iconic sandwiches in american food culture. The sandwich features a lightly toasted bread, crispy bacon and freshly chopped pieces of firm lettuce. This sandwich is appropriate in settings from a quick grab and go lunch to a dinner settings. It is versitle, tasty and meets the needs of anyone looking for a delicious bite to eat! </p>
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fresh White Bread</li>
      <li>Butter/Vegetable Oil</li>
      <li>Bacon</li>
      <li>Lettuce</li>
      <li>Tomato</li>
      <li>Mayonaisse or Garlic Aoili (Either are a fine choice)</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Instructions</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Heat a pan on medium temperature with butter until melted</li>
      <li>Toast a slice of bread in the butter until a the color is a light crispy brown.</li>
      <li>In a seperate pot, cook bacon for 10 minutes roughly until crunchy. Drain oil off bacon and set asside.</li>
      <li>Slice roma tomatoes in 1/8 inch thick slices. Two per sandwich is sufficient.</li>
      <li>Assemble sandwich, add a thin layer of garlic aoili to both pieced of toasted bread, add tomato, bacon and lettuce and then slice the sandwich in half and serve.</li>
    </ol>
